    <h1>Series</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Jiří Lebl · <a href="https://www.jirka.org/ra/">Basic Analysis I, Ch. 3</a> · CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>series</strong> converges if its sequence of partial sums converges. Absolute convergence implies convergence, but not vice versa. The comparison, ratio, and root tests give practical criteria. Power series converge inside a radius and diverge outside it.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Partial sums approaching a limit -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 180" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
